  "base_commit": "bf1cf69e24e3ede7d7053c17d47e381be959880e",
  "pr_number": 10324,
  "issue_number": 10322,
  "issue_title": "make_aware() silently mishandles spring-forward DST gap \u2014 crontab tasks scheduled in a non-existent local time are skipped or run with wrong UTC offset",
  "issue_body": "# Checklist\n- [x] I have verified that the issue exists against the `main` branch of Celery.\n- [x] This has already been asked to the [discussions forum](https://github.com/celery/celery/discussions) first.\n- [x] I have read the relevant section in the\n  [contribution guide](https://docs.celeryq.dev/en/main/contributing.html#other-bugs)\n  on reporting bugs.\n- [x] I have checked the [issues list](https://github.com/celery/celery/issues?q=is%3Aissue+label%3A%22Issue+Type%3A+Bug+Report%22+-label%3A%22Category%3A+Documentation%22)\n  for similar or identical bug reports.\n- [x] I have checked the [pull requests list](https://github.com/celery/celery/pulls?q=is%3Apr+label%3A%22PR+Type%3A+Bugfix%22+-label%3A%22Category%3A+Documentation%22)\n  for existing proposed fixes.\n- [x] I have checked the [commit log](https://github.com/celery/celery/commits/main)\n  to find out if the bug was already fixed in the main branch.\n- [x] I have included all related issues and possible duplicate issues\n  in this issue (If there are none, check this box anyway).\n- [ ] I have tried to reproduce the issue with [pytest-celery](https://docs.celeryq.dev/projects/pytest-celery/en/latest/userguide/celery-bug-report.html) and added the reproduction script below.\n\n## Mandatory Debugging Information\n\n- [ ] I have included the output of ``celery -A proj report`` in the issue.\n- [x] I have verified that the issue exists against the `main` branch of Celery.\n- [ ] I have included the contents of ``pip freeze`` in the issue.\n- [ ] I have included all the versions of all the external dependencies required\n  to reproduce this bug.\n\n## Optional Debugging Information\n\n- [x] I have tried reproducing the issue on more than one Python version\n  and/or implementation.\n- [x] I have tried reproducing the issue on more than one operating system.\n\n## Related Issues and Possible Duplicates\n\n#### Related Issues\n\n- #10107 \u2014 Hourly crontab skips execution during **fall-back** DST transition (the complementary issue; that PR introduced `_is_ambiguous` handling but did not address the spring-forward gap)\n\n#### Possible Duplicates\n\n- None\n\n## Environment & Settings\n\n**Celery version**: main (post-5.4)\n\n**Relevant config**:\n```python\nCELERY_TIMEZONE = \"US/Eastern\"  # or any DST-observing zone\nCELERY_ENABLE_UTC = True\n```\n\n# Steps to Reproduce\n\n## Required Dependencies\n\n- **Minimal Python Version**: 3.9\n- **Minimal Celery Version**: 5.3 (after pytz deprecation / ZoneInfo migration)\n- **Minimal Kombu Version**: N/A\n- **Minimal Broker Version**: N/A\n- **Minimal Result Backend Version**: N/A\n- **Minimal OS and/or Kernel Version**: Any\n- **Minimal Broker Client Version**: N/A\n- **Minimal Result Backend Client Version**: N/A\n\n### Python Packages\n\n<details>\n<summary><b><code>pip freeze</code> Output:</b></summary>\n<p>\ncelery @ git+https://github.com/celery/celery@main\npython-dateutil>=2.8\n</p>\n</details>\n\n## Minimally Reproducible Test Case\n\n<details>\n<p>\n\n```python\nfrom zoneinfo import ZoneInfo\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom dateutil import tz as dateutil_tz\nfrom celery.utils.time import make_aware\n\ntz = ZoneInfo(\"US/Eastern\")\n\n# March 10, 2024: clocks spring forward at 2:00 AM -> 3:00 AM\n# 2:30 AM does not exist in US/Eastern on this date\nnon_existent_dt = datetime(2024, 3, 10, 2, 30, 0)\n\n# Confirm it truly doesn't exist\nassert not dateutil_tz.datetime_exists(non_existent_dt.replace(tzinfo=tz)), \\\n    \"Expected non-existent time in spring-forward gap\"\n\nresult = make_aware(non_existent_dt, tz)\n\n# The UTC offset will be -05:00 (EST) instead of the correct post-transition -04:00 (EDT)\n# The function returns silently with no warning or error\nprint(result)\nprint(result.utcoffset())  # prints -1 day, 19:00:00 (i.e. -05:00, which is wrong)\n\n# To see the beat scheduler impact:\nfrom celery.schedules import crontab\nschedule = crontab(hour=2, minute=30, app=None)\n# On the spring-forward night, remaining_delta produces a next-run datetime\n# landing in the gap, which make_aware() resolves incorrectly,\n# causing the task to either be skipped or fire an hour late.\n```\n\n</p>\n</details>\n\n# Expected Behavior\n\n`make_aware()` should detect when a naive datetime falls inside a spring-forward DST gap (a time that does not exist in the given timezone) and advance the datetime to the first valid moment after the gap \u2014 consistent with how most DST-aware frameworks (Django, Arrow, pendulum) handle this case.\n\n`dateutil_tz.datetime_exists()` is already available via the existing `from dateutil import tz as dateutil_tz` import in `celery/utils/time.py` and can be used directly.\n\nProposed fix in `celery/utils/time.py`:\n\n```python\ndef make_aware(dt: datetime, tz: tzinfo) -> datetime:\n    \"\"\"Set timezone for a :class:`~datetime.datetime` object.\"\"\"\n    dt = dt.replace(tzinfo=tz)\n    if _is_ambiguous(dt, tz):\n        # Fall-back: two wall-clock instants map to the same local time.\n        # Pick the earlier UTC instant (fold=0, DST still active).\n        dt = min(dt.replace(fold=0), dt.replace(fold=1))\n    elif _can_detect_ambiguous(tz) and not dateutil_tz.datetime_exists(dt):\n        # Spring-forward gap: this local time does not exist.\n        # Advance to the post-transition instant (fold=1).\n        dt = dt.replace(fold=1)\n    return dt\n```\n\nA corresponding `_is_nonexistent()` helper (mirroring `_is_ambiguous()`) could also be added for clarity and testability.\n\n# Actual Behavior\n\n`make_aware()` only guards against ambiguous (fall-back) times via `_is_ambiguous()`. There is no equivalent check for non-existent (spring-forward) times.\n\nWhen a crontab's computed next-run datetime lands inside the spring-forward gap:\n\n1. `make_aware()` calls `dt.replace(tzinfo=tz)` on the non-existent time with no further correction.\n2. The resulting datetime carries the pre-transition UTC offset (e.g. `-05:00` EST instead of `-04:00` EDT).\n3. `remaining_estimate()` therefore computes a next-run time that is **one hour later than intended** in UTC.\n4. On the affected night the task either **fires one hour late** or is **silently skipped** entirely, with no log warning or exception raised.\n\nThis is the exact spring-forward counterpart to #10107 (fall-back skipping), but currently has no handling in the codebase.\n\n\n\nI WOULD LIKE TO WORK ON THIS ISSUE AND GET IT FIXED AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.\nPLEASE ASSIGN IT TO ME.",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-08T16:46:50Z",
